"title": "5103: Moses, significance of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5103: moses, significance of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Moses performed a number of major roles in the history of Israel. Many of these roles later found their perfection in Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>The roles of Moses</h2>\n<h3>As teacher</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:20\">EXO 18:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:10\">MAT 23:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:38\">JHN 1:38</a></p>\n<h3>As intercessor</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:11\">EXO 17:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:11\">EXO 32:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:13\">NUM 12:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:7\">NUM 21:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:23\">PSA 106:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:9\">JHN 17:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:25\">HEB 7:25</a></p>\n<h3>As servant of the LORD</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:1-Josh1:2\">JOS 1:1–1:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:6\">2CH 24:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:13\">ACT 3:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:5\">HEB 3:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:3\">REV 15:3</a></p>\n<h3>As prophet</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:6-Num12:8\">NUM 12:6–12:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:15\">DEU 18:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:10\">DEU 34:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:22\">ACT 3:22</a></p>\n<h3>As deliverer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:10\">EXO 3:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:35\">ACT 7:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:1\">GAL 5:1</a></p>\n<h3>As judge</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:13\">EXO 18:13</a></p>\n<h3>As writer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:4\">EXO 24:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:9\">DEU 31:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:27\">LUK 24:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:45\">JHN 1:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:46\">JHN 5:46</a></p>\n<h3>As shepherd</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:1\">EXO 3:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:20\">PSA 77:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:11\">JHN 10:11</a></p>\n<h3>As the friend of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:11\">EXO 33:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:17\">EXO 33:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:5\">MAT 17:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:20\">JHN 5:20</a></p>\n<h3>As the mediator of the law and the covenant</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:5-Exod19:6\">EXO 19:5–19:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:1-Deut6:3\">DEU 6:1–6:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:9\">DEU 31:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:6\">JOS 23:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:12\">2KI 18:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:19\">GAL 3:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:15\">HEB 9:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:24\">HEB 12:24</a></p>\n<h2>Characteristics of Moses</h2>\n<h3>He was a man of faith</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:13-Exod14:14\">EXO 14:13–14:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:24-Heb11:28\">HEB 11:24–11:28</a></p>\n<h3>He was not eloquent</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:10\">EXO 4:10</a></p>\n<h3>He understood that the law meant life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:46-Deut32:47\">DEU 32:46–32:47</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:17-Matt5:19\">MAT 5:17–5:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:17\">MAT 19:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:38\">ACT 7:38</a></p>\n<h3>He was passionate in his defence of the Lord's holiness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:19\">EXO 32:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:30\">NUM 16:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:45-Luke19:46\">LUK 19:45–19:46</a></p>\n<h3>He worked miracles that brought glory to God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:15-Exod14:18\">EXO 14:15–14:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:11\">JHN 2:11</a></p>\n<h2>Institutions established by Moses</h2>\n<h3>He fathers, and is identified with, the Judaic legal system</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:7-Josh1:8\">JOS 1:7–1:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:3\">1KI 2:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:2\">EZR 3:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:1\">NEH 13:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:45\">JHN 5:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:23\">JHN 7:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:9\">1CO 9:9</a></p>\n<h3>He inaugurates the ritual slaughter of the Passover lamb</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:21\">EXO 12:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:29\">JHN 1:29</a></p>\n<h3>He sprinkles the people with the blood of the covenant</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:8\">EXO 24:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:11\">LEV 17:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:28\">MAT 26:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:13-Heb9:14\">HEB 9:13–9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:28\">HEB 11:28</a></p>\n<h3>He orders the atonement sacrifice</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:46\">NUM 16:46</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:25\">ROM 3:25</a></p>\n<h2>Moses enters the glory of the LORD</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:17-Exod24:18\">EXO 24:17–24:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:29\">EXO 34:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:2\">MAT 17:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:7\">2CO 3:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:3-Rev15:4\">REV 15:3–15:4</a></p>\n<h2>Moses present at the transfiguration</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:4\">MRK 9:4</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:3\">MAT 17:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:30\">LUK 9:30</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ is superior to Moses</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:3\">HEB 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:5-Heb3:6\">HEB 3:5–3:6</a></p>",
